fields.description:
When attempting to create a volume larger than the maximum permitted size the error message does not reflect the cause of the failure:

{code}
> euca-create-volume -s 17 -z PARTI00
CreateVolumeType: com.eucalyptus.util.async.ConnectionException: Channel was closed before the response was received.:CreateStorageVolumeType:dad2aef5-09f5-4259-8762-2484188c3c6b:return=true:epoch=25:status=null
{code}

The following property controls the maximum permitted size:

{code}
PROPERTY	PARTI00.storage.maxvolumesizeingb	15
{code}

comments.body:
The originally reported message is not the typical error message for this condition:

{code}
CreateVolumeType: Failed to send message CreateStorageVolumeType to service StorageInternal because: Max Volume Size Limit Exceeded volume: vol-FF1D3E43
{code}
